      "title": "Set up",
      "content": "Let $U$ = undergraduates, $G$ = graduates, $P$ = postdoctoral students. The problem gives $U = 0.725P$, $G = 0.44U$, and $G = 6{,}380$. The goal is $U + P$."
    },
    {
      "title": "Solve",
      "content": "From $G = 0.44U$: $U = \\dfrac{6{,}380}{0.44} = 14{,}500$. From $U = 0.725P$: $P = \\dfrac{14{,}500}{0.725} = 20{,}000$. Sum: $14{,}500 + 20{,}000 = 34{,}500$."
    },
    {
      "title": "Answer",
      "content": "<strong>34500</strong> is correct."
    }
